Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.68,0:00:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess we're here.\NSuddenly find yourself where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.04,0:00:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's amazing.\NWell, this is the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.80,0:00:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,12th of a series of lectures in which we\Num intend to include everything you ever
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.48,0:00:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,need to know throughout all of time.\NAnd what did I do with it? Now, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.64,0:00:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,see. Here we have it right here.\NThis is all we need to know forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.44,0:00:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nwhat's unique about the um the lectures
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.35,0:01:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the lecture is the combination of\Nthe subjective and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.51,0:01:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which is nonlinear and um\Nand the linear which is the um Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.88,0:01:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm of reality.\NAnd what's been unique is that we had
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.79,0:01:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the advantage for the first time\Nof having a technique of doing spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.40,0:01:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,research which has never been done\Nbefore.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.43,0:01:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What people talk when they talk about\Nspiritual research, they really are
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.28,0:01:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about paleontology and\Narchaeology
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.96,0:01:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,where the great saints walked many\Ncenturies ago. that had nothing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.20,0:01:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with spiritual truth which is a reality\Na self-existent reality in the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.11,0:01:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So we had a means of exploring\Nunexplored realms
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.24,0:02:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which in itself was mindboggling\Nand whatever left was left of the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.92,0:02:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,was blown away for some time\Nand I had to retire from the world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.20,0:02:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,completely because\Nso we've shared things that are rather
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.80,0:02:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,astonishing and one reason we use\Nkinesiologic
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.64,0:02:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,test during the lecture is just to\Nconfirm things that seem outrageously
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.04,0:02:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,mind-boggling.\NWhen it's all put together, they seem,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.64,0:02:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh, yeah." But when you first hear it,\Nit may sound outrageous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, every month we discover something\Nnew and dazzling,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.08,0:02:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and I thought we'd just start with\Nsomething new and dazzling today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.59,0:02:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh,\Neverybody over 200, we'll ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.48,0:03:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody who calibrates over 200 goes\Nto a variety of heavens. Resist. Wow,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.92,0:03:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,folks.\NWe told you you're karmically all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.56,0:03:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your level of conscious when\Nyou're born
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.51,0:03:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the moment of death is\Npredestined from the moment you're born.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.48,0:03:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about death.\NAnd now we're giving you the good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We discovered that and I it just came to\Nme and I said, "Whoa,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.95,0:03:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,all over 200 go to a heaven because\Nthere's multiple heavens." Resist. And
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.68,0:03:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the heaven that you go to is aligned\Nwith your calibrated level of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.04,0:03:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. Resist.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.92,0:03:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that does seem to solve a lot of spirit\Nreligious conflict in which various
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.72,0:03:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,religious groups throughout time have\Nclaimed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.15,0:03:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that they have an exclusive uh claim on\Nheaven. And only if you follow their
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.31,0:04:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,rituals and pay their dues do you get\Ninto their heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.79,0:04:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the requirements are quite\Noutrageous. I don't know that I'd even
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.48,0:04:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,want to go to one of the heavens.\NI don't want to insult any religion, but
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.15,0:04:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,some of them\Nhave requirements to get into their
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.92,0:04:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven that I think are somewhat\Noutrageous
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.00,0:04:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,uh and undemocratic.\NSo they ex they claim correctly it turns
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.75,0:04:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,out correctly that to be admitted to\Ntheir heaven these requirements need to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,be followed.\NSimple enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.47,0:04:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who wish to be with others that\Nare similar to themsel in belief
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.80,0:04:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then\Ndo have a certain realm where they
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,congregate. So that all makes sense,\Ndoesn't it? that like goes to like
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.47,0:05:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which uh\Nis committed to certain principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.52,0:05:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then so there's a certain karmic\Ncalibration certain not calibration
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.12,0:05:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,vibration a certain frequency then and\Nwe said as you leave the body you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically find yourself in the realm\Nof your own vibration that's because
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.24,0:05:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what you identify with and are\Nattracted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.56,0:05:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So that should handle the afterlife I\Nthought which would be good for openers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.52,0:05:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The uh\Nthe fate of people who are less than 200
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.63,0:05:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is less fortunate.\NThe people less than 200 automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.44,0:05:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,go to heavens resist. No that is not so.\NH they go to other places but we would
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.08,0:06:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,not call them heavens. Uhhuh.\NHowever,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.91,0:06:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they go to a place with which they're\Nfamiliar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.00,0:06:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Neven that is not so bad, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're used to killing killing others\Nand torturing prisoners and things like
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that and you go on the other side, you\Nfind yourself right in that realm where
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.19,0:06:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all that goes on. So doesn't seem to you\Nlike hell. It seems to you like home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.36,0:06:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,These people less than 200. We've never\Nasked this before. We have permission to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.80,0:06:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,ask this. Resist. Just find themselves\Nwhat they consider to be home. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.60,0:06:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So much for the fears of heaven and\Nhell. And
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:06:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes sense that one would find\Noneself
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.72,0:07:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in the realm uh to which one is\Ncommitted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.03,0:07:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Npeople sometimes say, "Well, it's too
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.72,0:07:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,bad you have these calibrated levels\Nbecause people can use it to say one
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.52,0:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is better than another." Well, if\Nyou do, that's your problem. It's not my
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,problem.\NYou can say having a Cadillac is better
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,than a Buick. I mean this is all in your\Nmind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.00,0:07:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh it isn't that one thing is better\Nthan another. Each thing is a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.75,0:07:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,stratification of that which it is.\NSpiritually evolved people tend to look
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.28,0:07:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,down on the lower levels and say isn't\Nthat awful?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.24,0:07:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,These levels below 200 they'll serve\Nserve
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.03,0:07:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in their own way because\Nyou see each thing is relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.19,0:07:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So angriness we said that the human life\Non this planet is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.91,0:08:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of such a range there's an infinite\Nnumber of possibilities
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.72,0:08:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore\Nfor the people down here this is high.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.72,0:08:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? So instead of disparaging that\Npeople live
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.24,0:08:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in less than what we consider\Nspiritually idealistic levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.16,0:08:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness\Nbecause this world is and I've forgotten
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.24,0:08:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the world word\Nit'll come to me um
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.47,0:08:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know where you go to work off bad\Nkarma and earn good karma. What's the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.44,0:08:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,name of that?\N>> Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.76,0:08:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Purgatorial.\N>> Oh purgatorial. Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.51,0:08:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is sort of a purgatorial.\NI'm not going to call it purgatory. You
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.83,0:08:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,don't say he said it was purgatory. It's\Npurgatorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.80,0:09:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And that we have the whole range from\Nthe ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.68,0:09:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,both ends of the scale.\NSo those people who live in rage,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.12,0:09:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred, and anger,\Nhere's rage, hatred, and anger. Can you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.16,0:09:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,imagine what a great high that is?\NLook, I I I treat lots of girls like
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that. And angryness, everything makes\Nthem angry. They come in for the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.20,0:09:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,staffing and I say, "What's the matter?\NI'm angry."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.76,0:09:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything makes her angry.\NHaving to wait to come in makes her
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.83,0:09:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,angry. Being at staff meeting makes her\Nangry. Having to leave the staff meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.95,0:09:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,makes her angry. You know what I mean?\NWhat they have for breakfast makes her
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.27,0:09:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,angry. They live in the angry box.\NAnd they're always hitting each other
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.32,0:09:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and being angry.\NAnd you say, why would they want to live
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.24,0:09:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in angryness? To us, angryness is sort\Nof an unpleasant sensation. And you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.68,0:09:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,"Dear Lord, please help me see this\Ndifferently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.27,0:10:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me out of this anger." And\Nspiritually we sort of feel ashamed that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.76,0:10:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we sunk down to the lover of anger. This\Nis a high to people in apathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.08,0:10:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we don't understand a lot of uh\Nmusic, gangster rock and hate rock or
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.44,0:10:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call it? Kill your sister\Nand rape your mother and stab your aunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Rape your neighbors. I mean, you know,\Ngreat stuff like that. And we say, man,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.32,0:10:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that is really degenerate. You know what\NI mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.32,0:10:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,uh these whole groups that make and\Nthey'll tell you the reason they do is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.39,0:10:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they make huge amounts of money.\NWell, making huge amounts of money,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.72,0:10:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,folks,\Nis a heck of a lot better than being at
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.64,0:10:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the bottom,\Napathetic, penniles, povertystricken,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.95,0:10:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,laying there, dying of starvation with\NAIDS, Bafraa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.07,0:11:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you come in at this level then\Ngetting up to greed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.68,0:11:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,anything is better than huh\Nyou so now you understand the attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.80,0:11:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of this\Nself-righteous anger
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.20,0:11:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,this kind of music they play what do\Nthey call it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.88,0:11:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there sort of an angriness rap yeah you\Ndid this to me. You guys did that to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.32,0:11:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm going to get eat with you.\NAnd they they feed off that crap. You
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.32,0:11:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "What's with these people? Are they\Nsmoking something or what?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.24,0:11:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nyou people are going to get it and you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.36,0:11:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,did it to me and now you Yeah, you're\Ngetting yours and we're all getting even
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'm angry.\NAnd that's prideful, too. That's really
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.00,0:11:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cocky. And the names of the groups are\Nusually the super supers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.48,0:12:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The king of the supers.\NThe super super king of the supers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.48,0:12:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Supers best.\NAll right. Now we can have compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.83,0:12:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,for that because you see coming out of\Napathy. Look at all these people down
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.80,0:12:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,here. The one thing we didn't get done\Nfor the lectures that I wanted to do is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.20,0:12:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the map of the world in which we\Ncalibrate the different continents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the different countries within the\Ncontinents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.36,0:12:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a map that's really critical to\Nour State Department.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.44,0:12:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see who the heck you're dealing\Nwith, folks, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.16,0:12:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,democracy, what does democracy mean to\Nsomebody who calibrates at 45,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.60,0:12:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,who's starving to death in the streets?\NDemocracy is an idealistic
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.92,0:12:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,pomposity.\NIt's a pomposity to people who live on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.27,0:12:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that level.\NUnreal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.32,0:13:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And it doesn't work.\NIt never dawns on Americans that many
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.27,0:13:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,countries, in fact, even continents are\Nnot even ready for democracy. Wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.36,0:13:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,know what to do with it. Has no value to\Nthem. If you give it to them, they'll
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.51,0:13:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly destroy it\Nbecause it has no value. Uh democracy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.80,0:13:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean much of anything till you\Nget for around the 400s or high 300s. It
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.95,0:13:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean anything. It's stupid.\NMany countries think to let people run
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.27,0:13:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,around doing and saying what they want.\NIt was really ultra stupid and America
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.95,0:13:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,deser gets what it deserves, you know.\NAll right. So begin then to be able to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.39,0:13:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,accept the whole range of consciousness\Nwithout a better than a greater than a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.88,0:13:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,right wrong moralistic\Nuh positionality about it
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.39,0:13:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,if you are in apathy. So the great\Ngoonas you know piti comes out in three
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.36,0:14:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,gonas you know tamas rajas and satta\Nclassically in Sanskrit tamas
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.60,0:14:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is that of lethargy and resistance and\Nthese people starve to death and they
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.12,0:14:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have the energy when you walk\Nthrough their neighborhoods it's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.16,0:14:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,littered with trash\Nyou know you can tell by the energy of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.56,0:14:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the neighborhood and and it pulls it\Npulls that to apathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.00,0:14:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember seeing one of the most\Nbeautiful waterfalls
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.00,0:14:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,uh I guess it's in this hemisphere\Nin this hemisphere and uh after a long
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.07,0:14:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,trail ride to get there and all and\Nhere's this gorgeous waterfall with a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.00,0:14:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,pool at the bottom and there's you know\Nthere's broken down plastic tricycles
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.00,0:14:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and paper bags and crap all over the\Nplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.56,0:14:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the people indig the people\Nindigenous to the area in apathy you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.80,0:15:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have the energy or the interest to\Npick up trash around you. You just kick
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.72,0:15:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it around and walk by it.\NYou don't have any pride there in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.27,0:15:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,pride. You don't clean up the trash\Nuntil you get out of here starting to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.39,0:15:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,want something better. Get angry about\Nthe miserableness of your life and have
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.83,0:15:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,enough pride to pick up the trash.\NSo the first sign of apathy then is the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.12,0:15:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,so-called broken window\Ntheory of sociology.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.63,0:15:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The first factory window that you don't\Nfix attracts the next broken window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.83,0:15:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Attracts the graffiti, attracts the\Nmice, attracts the drug addicts,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.48,0:15:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,attracts murder, apathy, suicide,\Npoverty.
