Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.35,0:34:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is a quality.\NWe call it a quality. We project that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.39,0:34:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,thought onto it. Is a quality of\Ncontext.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.35,0:35:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego then identifies with content\Nwhereas its reality is coming as is is a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.24,0:35:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of context\Nin the meditative or contemplative state
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.80,0:35:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of which in which we constantly\Nsurrender content as it arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.83,0:35:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you in the 12th step have been\Nthe 12th step, you know the third step,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.24,0:35:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to totally and surrender\Nall to God at every instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.24,0:35:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As this comes up, we totally surrender\Nit to God. We do so in the interest of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.44,0:35:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the context.\NThe ego would have you think that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.28,0:35:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind, let's say, the mind and ego\Nare one of the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.28,0:35:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And karma, karma, mind, and ego are all\Nthe same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.96,0:36:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all the same thing. You don't\Nhave to worry about that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.35,0:36:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You are your karma.\NAnd how are you your karma? The form
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.40,0:36:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that your mind takes in the ego\Nstructure. So
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.92,0:36:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,alo that's one reason Jesus didn't talk\Nabout it much because if you just solve
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.72,0:36:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,your problems in the present you're\Nsolving your karma because because you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.24,0:36:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are your karmic problem that's why\Nyou're here you know just worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.24,0:36:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what you are now that solves all the\Nkarma because the way you are now is due
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.83,0:36:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to all the karma. So if you do it now,\Nyou undone your karma. So you don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.96,0:36:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to worry about karma unless you're\Nreally hung up on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.83,0:36:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally we get people that are hung\Nup on their karma and I tell them, look,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.56,0:36:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,get a one of these regressionists. They\Ntake you back to previous lifetime and
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.96,0:36:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you get to reexperience it. Sometimes\Nit's really quite relieving and quite
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.48,0:36:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,amazing. And some of those techniques\Nare quite effective,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.80,0:37:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,very good. Sometimes they resolve your\Ndoubt about something. Oh, now I see why
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.28,0:37:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like something rather. So, yeah.\NWell, I wouldn't either under the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.16,0:37:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstances that he recalls, you know.\NAll right. At least at least you can
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.56,0:37:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,feel better about it.\NIf you assiduously,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.24,0:37:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,assiduously,\Ncommittedly,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.59,0:37:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,fervently,\Nconstantly surrender everything as it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.59,0:37:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,comes up to God\Nand stay related to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.56,0:37:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the generality of that which is around\Nyou rather than the specifics.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.76,0:37:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do this devotedly,\None eventually transcends the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.88,0:37:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,identification with with the content of\Nthe ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.68,0:38:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We know you you'll be able to tell when\Nit's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.16,0:38:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your friends will say you're strange for\None thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.59,0:38:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Your friends say you're strange. you\Nknow, you're making very good progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.28,0:38:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You really need to see a doctor. That's\Na real good.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.00,0:38:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, he's really flipped out. He's\Nlosing it, you know? He's into this
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.44,0:38:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,whole God business. And\Nleft home wife and kids and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.56,0:38:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So\Nwe can see just from the emotions you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.32,0:38:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,see here's the process going on in\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.48,0:38:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nwe see why these states are high. These
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.00,0:38:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,people are into destruction. They're\Nclose to death dispondency. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.16,0:38:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,withdrawn. They become slaves. They are\Nthe slaves of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.35,0:38:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see then the ego inflation of\Npride uh gives you a feeling that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.04,0:39:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody and that's why they walk around\Nso cocky. Now you feel like somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.96,0:39:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to steal this feeling\Nhere without actually being this and it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.20,0:39:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't work.\NSo pride is easily knocked off of its
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.07,0:39:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,pride leadth to downfall because it's\Nvulnerable. It's not based on reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.44,0:39:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an inflation. It's an inflation.\NBoom. Boom. Boom. Boom. They pop up with
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.92,0:39:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,inflation. So, it's fake. So, on the\Nother hand, it feels good. It feels
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.24,0:39:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,good. Pride feels quite good.\NUh, but then pride meets the test of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.59,0:39:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's actually courage.\NAnd that's why the United States Marines
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.96,0:39:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,enlist you on the level of pride, but\Nthen they move you to the level of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.80,0:39:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,courage cuz pride won't hold up on the\Nbattlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.52,0:40:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride chickens out and runs. So\Nthe Marines want you to move from pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.83,0:40:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,being proud of being a Marine, coming\Nout of a lesser socioeconomic status.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.44,0:40:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And for once you're a gentleman.\NSo you salute them out of pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.96,0:40:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But then they train you. So the training\Nof the service is to take you out of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.68,0:40:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,pridefulness, out of apathy, out of\Nself-centeredness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.88,0:40:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and into courage.\NAnd so
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.72,0:40:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,traditionally throughout the centuries\Nthe army the enlistment in the service
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.40,0:40:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the country has been one of the\Npathways to integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.56,0:40:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the pathways to integrity.\NOf course it's possible to fail it and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.04,0:41:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,crash.\NOh. So
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.00,0:41:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to answer however by this\Nexplanation the objection that one level
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.56,0:41:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is better than another. It's not better\Nthan another. It's different than
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.24,0:41:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,another and it's serving a different\Npurpose. Serving a different purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.04,0:41:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see\Na pres you can't have a president of the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.48,0:41:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,United States down here, you know, and\Nyou can't have a president up there
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.88,0:41:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,either.\NWhat kind of a president would a guy be
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.20,0:41:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in 600?\NBoys, boys, let's not fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.16,0:41:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I say peace\Nto North Korea. Peace to Afghanistan.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.31,0:41:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> There's a lot around like that.\NI don't understand what she's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.88,0:42:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Gandhi Gandhi Gandhi\N>> Gandhi calibrated you know at 700
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.07,0:42:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Gandhi stood against the British Empire.\NThe British Empire at the time that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.59,0:42:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Gandhi stood up to it calibrated about\N190. If I remember it was up
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.35,0:42:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,British Empire was around in 190 that\Nthe position the position of the British
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.16,0:42:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Empire at the time was about 190\Nresistance. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.96,0:42:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride of the empire\Nhottiness. Hottiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.11,0:42:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The British aristocracy was notably\Nhotty
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.88,0:42:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as are all most aristocracies.\Nwhich cost them their heads of course
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.56,0:42:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,famous Zars and their families etc.\NLet them meet cake. So
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.40,0:43:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mahatma Gandhi however calibrated at 700\Nand you see Gandhi didn't attack the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.72,0:43:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,British Empire nor did he run from it.\NSo he he took a a position of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.20,0:43:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uh standing for truth.\NThe question is always when you're
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.64,0:43:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,attacked what should your position be?\NAnd the position should be to stand up
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.24,0:43:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for truth to be answerable and to stand\Nfor truth
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.56,0:43:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever the consequences.\NThat's what Mahatma did. Mandi did he
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.44,0:43:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,merely confronted the British Empire\Nfrom a position of 700 the British
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.11,0:43:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Empire calibrated at 190.\NSo that confrontation between 700 which
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.35,0:43:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is enormously powerful\Nyou see these rings of power out there
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.80,0:44:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as you get up to 6700 and all\Nthe context become is the power.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.59,0:44:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So you just stand there. We said that\Npower just stands there. It doesn't do
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.83,0:44:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,anything like gravity.\NCan you imagine if you tried to measure
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.40,0:44:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the influence on of gravity\Nand all its multitudinous expressions?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.20,0:44:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The figure would be incalculable, so\Nimmense.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.56,0:44:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd have to weigh every object on the\Nplanet and put them all together and we
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.16,0:44:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,would come up with a fantastic number.\NIt does all that just by standing there,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.16,0:44:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,just by being what it is. Gravity\Ndoesn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.31,0:44:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,700 is a very powerful field.\NSo 700 just stood there and stood for
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.56,0:44:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity.\NAnd then the British Empire at 190 ran
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.56,0:45:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,up against the brick wall of power at\N700.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.96,0:45:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, Gandhi defeated the\NBritish Empire without a shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.44,0:45:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Gorbachev defeated\Ncomm the communist
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.88,0:45:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,monolithic\Nregime
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.04,0:45:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,also without firing a shot. There was no\Ngiant Russian revolution that put down
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.92,0:45:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the communist\Nempire. It fell. It fell apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.83,0:45:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's in great disarray because it's\Nnowhere near capable of handling
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.59,0:45:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,democracy.\NWe'll have to find some means probably
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.76,0:45:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,few maybe go back to feudal times.\NThat's pretty good as a starting point.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.64,0:45:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Feudal times is where all of modern\Ncivilization did start from at one time,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.48,0:45:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't it?\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.35,0:46:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between power and force\Nthen is that power accomplishes
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.31,0:46:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the quality of that which\Nit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.59,0:46:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to do anything.\NWhat does the spiritual aspirant
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.20,0:46:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,do for the world?\NWhat they do for the world is a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.20,0:46:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of that which they become.\NRequires no effort whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.00,0:46:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't doesn't have to do anything\Nexcept to be
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.28,0:46:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,your own potential.\NSo as spirituality evolves then what
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.92,0:46:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,happens is the power of the context the\Nfield begins to shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.00,0:46:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We see whole continents, whole\Nneighborhoods, whole countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.96,0:47:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,counties, towns,\Nneighborhoods within the town dominated
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.00,0:47:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,by certain energy fields. That energy\Nfield now becomes more important
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.04,0:47:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,than the content.\NYou know it. The minute you walk into
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.00,0:47:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it, the hair goes up on the back of your\Nhead. you know you're in trouble even
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.83,0:47:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,though there's nobody threatening you on\Nthe street. This is not a safe space.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.48,0:47:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You get that?\NCertain neighborhoods that demented
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.11,0:47:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in them. You get that\Nthere are other places on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.56,0:47:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,where nobody would even think of\Ngraffiti. I've been in great and
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.59,0:47:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,beautiful places\Nhad they been located elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.48,0:47:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in which there is no graffiti\Nunlike the subway in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.31,0:47:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody ever ride the subway system in\NNew York?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.88,0:48:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Covered with graffiti vulgarity.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.88,0:48:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. What I really wanted to\Nemphasize today was the value that each
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.59,0:48:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of these things serves its own purpose.\NYou see, each of these things serves its
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.28,0:48:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,own purpose. Each one of these things\Nhas a conccomant emotion. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.16,0:48:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We disparage that which is below the\Nlevel below these levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.35,0:48:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,In more advanced spiritual work, of\Ncourse, the the greatest significance
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.16,0:48:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest significance is not over on\Nthe right hand side. The greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.31,0:48:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,significance is\Nover on the left hand side
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.68,0:48:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nwe begin to experience how
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.20,0:48:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this evolves\Nthrough spiritual understanding. And so
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.28,0:48:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the real focus of the spiritual aspirant\Nis how to overcome the residuals of the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.92,0:49:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,old animal within your brain. How to\Nstop identifying with that. How to stop
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.11,0:49:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,condemning yourself, feeling guilty\Nabout it. How to accept and love the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.88,0:49:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,little animal.\NIf you're spiritually oriented,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.55,0:49:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,everything with everything in the world\Nserves you. Everything in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.76,0:49:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,serves you.\NThe other night, we were watching a
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.88,0:49:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,video of the greatest uh tiger\Ntrainer in the world. I think he's
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.31,0:49:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Russian or Yugoslavian. Slavic, I think.\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.16,0:49:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he handles 10 or 11 wild Bengal tigers\Nall at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.00,0:49:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He adores them.\NYou feel the profound intense
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.04,0:49:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,love that he has for him. So his power,\NI told you I'd put this where you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.04,0:50:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,see it.\NHis power over the animals
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.59,0:50:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is his intense love. He's aware of who\Nhe is. He's aware of who they are and
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.52,0:50:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,they know it.\NSo when you watch him work 10 or 12
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.48,0:50:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,tigers at once, they all move in unison.\NHe has them almost spellbound
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.40,0:50:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,by the power of his love for them.\NHowever,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.92,0:50:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,at no time does he forget that they are\Nbasically a wild animal and if you push
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.80,0:50:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,him, he'll kill you.\NA very interesting lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.35,0:50:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At no time does he turn his back\Nor is he neglectful
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.88,0:50:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or does he go into denial that they will\Nkill you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.92,0:51:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true. The most domesticated tamed\Nwild animal if provoked at the right
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.20,0:51:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,moment will eat you up.\NWe mentioned that case history in one of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.96,0:51:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the earlier lectures.\NIn that case, the lion ate her out of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.76,0:51:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,love.\NBut
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.35,0:51:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,his concern was not that tigers would\Neat them out of love, but that he would
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.64,0:51:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,provoke them.\NSo he, you see, you can love everything
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.35,0:51:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet not be naive.\NThat's the downside of the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.83,0:51:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside of the 500s\Nis
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.11,0:51:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you walk in a world of love. Only love\Nis real. The only lovingness is what you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.59,0:51:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,see. Lovingness is what you experience.\NIn the beginning, there's a great naive
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.07,0:51:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to it.\NSpiritual awareness like other things
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.20,0:52:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,goes through various degrees of\Nmaturity.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.80,0:52:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And the early adolescent is enthused\Nabout spirituality and goes around hoo
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.11,0:52:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,la and praying for peace and sort of\Nfairy land of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.68,0:52:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside of that is an extreme\Nvulnerability. The naivee.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.24,0:52:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the tiger trainer is not naive.\NAnd yet his love is intense. His love is
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.59,0:52:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so intense. These tigers all behave\Nout of respect for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.40,0:52:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\Nas a teacher, the purpose of today's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.28,0:52:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture is to prepare you for the\Ndownside of what will come up if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.28,0:52:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually seriously committed.\NIf you run around to lectures, read
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.52,0:52:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,books here and there, and play around\Nwith the astral realm, get channelings
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.35,0:53:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that, you won't have to deal\Nwith this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.00,0:53:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're serious, the downside will\Ncome up. All right. There is that which
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.16,0:53:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is opposed to spiritual truth\Nand it has dominated mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.59,0:53:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,until the late 1980s. You remember the\Nlevel of consciousness of mankind until
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.83,0:53:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the late 1980s was 190. That means those\Nenergies which oppose God, deny God and
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.35,0:53:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,would rather\Nhave control of you and uh your beloveds
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.52,0:53:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,did dominate this\Nplanet until the late 1980s.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.55,0:53:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then for reasons\Nnot completely or totally known, the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.11,0:54:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level jumped to 207.\NAs you evolve spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.16,0:54:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you see your power, the not your power,\Nbut the power of your your energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.40,0:54:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your aura, whatever you call call it um\Nbecomes more and more powerful begins to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.55,0:54:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,dominate\Nand that which was used to dominating
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.28,0:54:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and controlling\Nuntil very recent times is therefore or
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.20,0:54:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,threatened by every spiritual aspirant.\NEveryone who reaches unconditional love
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.55,0:54:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then\Ndiminishes the domain of that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.68,0:54:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,non- integrous diminishes its control.\NConsequently, one becomes the target for
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.80,0:54:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is that is non-integrous and\Nwould like to entrap you in its control.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.88,0:54:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So the downside of the 500s is that\Nnaivity
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.68,0:55:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in which you love everything and see\Neverybody as lovable
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.31,0:55:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a consequence become blind.\NMany are the gurus of great renown both
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.80,0:55:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,dead and alive today who reached the\Nhigh of the mid mid usually the mid 500s
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.24,0:55:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and were taken down one after another\Ntheir numbers are rather shocking
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.44,0:55:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at one time calibrate 520 540\Nnow 180 huh
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.44,0:55:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens?\NYou see, the tiger trainer does not
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.52,0:55:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,pretend\Npretend that the tiger won't kill you
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.83,0:55:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,under if you ignore his in inner nature.\NHe demonstrates to me that you can love
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.44,0:56:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and still be aware of the downside of\Nwhat you're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.76,0:56:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think you can turn over your\Ntrust fund to anybody who wanders down
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.04,0:56:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the street and says he'd like to do it\Nfor you, you will soon be a poor person.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.48,0:56:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I trust everybody.\NI only believe in holiness and love.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.68,0:56:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, folks,\Nhow many people's retirement funds got
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.55,0:56:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sucked in by that one\Nnot long ago? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.52,0:56:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, the downside of the 500s,\Nunconditional love doesn't mean to be
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.79,0:56:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,blind.\NDoesn't mean to be blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.48,0:56:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Be aware that all this is out here.\NAnd frankly, it wants to get you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.72,0:57:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to tell you that\NI want you cuz
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.52,0:57:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to control you. I want your money\Nand I want power of you and you want you
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.72,0:57:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to sign up. You can stand for what you\Nare without necessarily provoking them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.04,0:57:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I say this is because\Nin this
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.07,0:57:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,experience quote which the world calls\Npersonal.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.68,0:57:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a thing did happen more than once.\NIt can happen in the non-material world
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.55,0:57:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and of for those who are spiritually\Ncommitted the danger is one of spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.40,0:57:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,seduction.\NWe're going to talk about the traps
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.64,0:57:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,along the way and then we're going to\Nlead up to the final doorway. But you
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.11,0:58:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,don't get to the final doorway without\Ngoing through the 500s in various
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.07,0:58:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,places. So I'll tell you\Nas tourists what the traps are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.79,0:58:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The tourist traps in the 500s.\NThe trusting, sweet,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.48,0:58:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,loving, adorable old lady.\NThey love to take your money.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.24,0:58:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid, I was always looking\Nfor a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.16,0:58:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So one day one time in the it said uh\Nthe saleserson wanted so you know I'm 16
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.48,0:58:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or 17 18 what I need a summer job in\Nsummer break from school or college
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.28,0:58:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever it was. So the idea was this\Nguy would train you to sell peanut
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.64,0:58:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,machines, you know, the kind you put a\Npenny into them. At those days they were
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.20,0:59:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,selling for $25. So the idea was you\Nadvertise how to make a lot of money and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.59,0:59:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. All these retired farmers will buy\Nthese machines for $25
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.11,0:59:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and you tell them look you go there once\Na month, take your money out
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.59,0:59:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or you drive around to all your machines\Nand you empty all the money out. So this
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.88,0:59:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,guy figured, gee, there's an ad on TV\Nright now about this ATMs or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.28,0:59:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Another sucker bait sound like to me.\NUh, so
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.52,0:59:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what you don't tell them is the peanut\Nmachine, if it empties every couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.04,0:59:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,years, it's going to be lucky.\NHow often do you think a peanut machine
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.55,0:59:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,empties? It empties this year, you're\Nlucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.11,0:59:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All these peanut machines, he thinks all\Nthe money's coming in. So this guy was
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.44,0:59:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,obviously a con man. See? So\NI I've had an uneasy feeling about this,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.35,0:59:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, and uh but I mean I said to\Nhim, "Well, what about these farmers?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.35,0:59:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This is I mean this is their retirement\Nmoney, their nestic they're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.55,1:00:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,live on the rest of their life."\NHe said, "Well, if we don't get it,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.92,1:00:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody else will."\NYou got it. There you go. So the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.68,1:00:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,rationalization is always there. The\Nrationalization is always there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.44,1:00:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Happily, I had enough integrity not to\Nget sucked into that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.55,1:00:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But um so they're out there. Now in the\Nspiritual world, the seduction takes
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.88,1:00:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,place in a different way.\NHow should we explain it?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.52,1:00:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My concern is that\Nmy own students be forewarned.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.04,1:00:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lack of education. You say how\Ncan people who was up at 540 or
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.20,1:00:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,something uh fall for the seduction of\Nfame, money, power,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.55,1:01:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,material goods, trappings.\NIt's because something was missing in
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.16,1:01:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,their spiritual education.\NYou could say, "Well, it's their fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.79,1:01:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They should have."\NYeah. But nobody forewarned them. So, I
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.92,1:01:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,don't want to go to my deathbed\Nthinking, "Oh my god, what I didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.44,1:01:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,say."\NIf you get suckered in, I feel it's my
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.44,1:01:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,uh karmic responsibility, you know.\NThough
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.83,1:01:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is glamorous,\Nspiritual seduction takes the form of a
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.04,1:01:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,glamour. A lot of times there's drama,\Nthere's theater, there's fancy titles,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.83,1:01:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,fancy clothing.\NI hate to say it, but most of them come
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.35,1:01:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,from India.\NThe reason is India is old at this.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.04,1:02:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Old at it. They've got it down so slick\Nthat you wouldn't know a swami from a
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.83,1:02:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,swimming.\NYou see truth is in it is is not in need
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.40,1:02:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of any trappings. Truth is not\Ninterested in seducing anybody,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.44,1:02:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,impressing anybody, glamorizing anybody.\NTruth is sufficient unto itself. It
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.76,1:02:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,comes not from elsewhere. Therefore, you\Nneed nothing out there. Truth has no
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.96,1:02:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,external teacher. There's no other\Nentity telling me what to say. Somebody
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.79,1:02:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,once said, "How do you channel all\Nthat?"
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.68,1:02:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's funny. Anyway,\Nthe knowingness is innate
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.59,1:02:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to speak with such authority. Do you\Nrealize the karmic consequences
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.88,1:03:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of speaking an error?\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.20,1:03:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,no, the truth comes from within. It is\Nnot given from elsewhere. There is no
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.11,1:03:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,other.\NAll the way through to the infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.88,1:03:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,presence in which only the oness is.\NNo other entities along the way. No
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.48,1:03:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,saints, no\Nbabas, no angels,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.59,1:03:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,no others. There is no other.\NNo celestial teachers
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.24,1:03:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,arose.\NRadical non-duality dispenses with all
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.92,1:03:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that.\NThose are all sidetracks. Those are all
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.68,1:03:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,illusions.\Nthat which appears mystical, magical,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.44,1:03:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and you know it's coming when you hear\Nthe oo and the o's.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.03,1:04:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Baba, so and so. Whoa.\NYou know what that means? That means
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.52,1:04:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that person has been glamorized.\NGlamorized.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.44,1:04:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I get letters every day. They're\Nheartbreaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.48,1:04:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,every day usually with a picture of some\Nguru
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.96,1:04:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,who was a descendant of\Nyou know they list all kinds of famous
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.28,1:04:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,names in history and this person is\Ngoing to save mankind and this person
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.52,1:04:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,believe there is or not can undo all\Nyour negative karma
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.16,1:04:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,this person is an avatar who will undo\Nall your negative karma
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.88,1:04:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and has millions of f followers in India\Nthis is a routine letter I get every day
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.11,1:04:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it's always a different swami your guru\Nhas millions of followers in India
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.28,1:04:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 290\Nover and over this comes up
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.31,1:05:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,mama this sells mama and baba baba this\Nand mama that
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.96,1:05:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the great mother of India is going to\Nsave all mankind she calibrates at 300
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.64,1:05:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you that\NI thought so this was disturbing for a
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.31,1:05:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,while I thought you know spiritual\Nresearch I wish I'd never even started
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.11,1:05:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was perfectly happy in a state\Nof bliss. Frankly,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.68,1:05:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not the contract. The contract\Nwas to share with that which I've
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.24,1:05:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,discovered for the good of all.\NMy that's my contract with God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.00,1:05:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that how can this be? one after\Nanother gurus you know we're calibrating
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.03,1:05:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand things for the\Nnext book after I and uh over and over
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.92,1:05:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,well-known teachers spiritual teachers\Nat one time 520 540 most of them were in
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.52,1:06:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the high mid mid 500s\Nand now 180
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.03,1:06:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,disparity we were getting different\Nnumbers on the same teacher
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.92,1:06:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When they're young, they were this and\Nnow they're this. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.55,1:06:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The world doesn't know that.\NOften the early writings are if you
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.00,1:06:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate them quite high,\Nthe teacher now is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.03,1:06:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How can this be? Hm. Well,\Nhow can the teacher is only 280 be be
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.52,1:06:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the savior of millions of India? The\Ngreat s the great avatar. It's going to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.48,1:06:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,undo all your negative karma and save\Nmankind.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.03,1:06:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter infers that I should quickly\Nrun and see this person get saved or
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.72,1:06:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,something.\NWell, because didn't make sense till I
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.35,1:07:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,realized that 290 to people down here is\Nlike a god.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.40,1:07:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you worship somebody who has\Nintegrity,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.00,1:07:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,confidence, speaks of love, is concerned\Nabout you and your welfare. This is a
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.31,1:07:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,shock.\NPeople live down here
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.20,1:07:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they are like a saint.\NSo okay that explained it then.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.20,1:07:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So they are great whatever their\Ncalibration is in that they serve the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.31,1:07:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,world in that capacity.\NSo that explained that dilemma.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.44,1:07:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it's important not to be not\Nto vary. You see, straight and narrow is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.92,1:08:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the way.\NThe Buddha said the middle path, not too
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.03,1:08:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,far this way, not too far this way.\NStraight and narrow is the way
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.64,1:08:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to be committed to integrity. Then be\Nforewarned that that which
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.55,1:08:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is glamorous,\Nimpressive,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.48,1:08:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,theatrical,\Na whole production
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.92,1:08:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that has a hierarchy that you can buy\Nyour way into
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.64,1:08:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is out after your naivity.\NThat which comes from absolute truth has
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.48,1:08:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,no need of trappings. What is the\Npurpose of trappings and performance and
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.08,1:08:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,theater?\NThat's to entrance the audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.04,1:08:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth has no interest in an audience at\Nall.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.96,1:09:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If nobody hears, nobody's here. It's no\Nit's all the same. Makes no difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.79,1:09:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no gain, no loss.\NSo a lot of times you go around to
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.15,1:09:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,various spiritual things and there is\Nall kinds of theater, entertainment,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.88,1:09:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,drama,\Nritual,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.96,1:09:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,smoke and incense and the whole deal\Nthat goes with it. Mystical rituals.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.44,1:09:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You better calibrate it first.\NThe best thing to do is calibrate it. Of
